Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper discusses the use of a one-tap normalized least-mean-square algorithm for carrier phase recovery in optical fiber communication systems. This involves the analysis of feedback mechanisms and estimation of bit-error-rate, which are relevant topics in information theory.
2. cs.OH (Optimization and Control): The use of algorithms for carrier phase recovery in optical communication systems involves optimization and control of the signal processing parameters. 
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses the use of coherent optical transmission systems, which are relevant to networking and internet architecture.
4. cs.COMM (Communication and Networking): The paper discusses the use of feedback mechanisms and signal processing algorithms in optical fiber communication systems, which are relevant topics in communication and networking.
5. cs.PHYS (Physics): The paper discusses the compensation of intrinsic laser phase noise and equalization enhanced phase noise in optical fiber communication systems, which are relevant topics in physics.
